---

## Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/selenium-login-api.git
cd selenium-login-api
```

Create a virtual environment (recommended):

```bash
python -m venv .venv
```

Activate the virtual environment.

### Windows

```bash
.venv\Scripts\activate
```

### Linux / macOS

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate
```

Install the dependencies:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## Running the API

Start the Flask server:

```bash
python app.py
```

The API will be available at:

```
http://127.0.0.1:5000
```

---

## Endpoint

### POST `/testSelenium2`

Receives a list of credentials and performs automated login attempts.

### Example Request

```json
{
  "credentials": [
    {
      "email": "tomsmith",
      "password": "SuperSecretPassword!"
    },
    {
      "email": "invalidUser",
      "password": "wrongPassword"
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Example Response

```json
{
  "status": "ok",
  "intentos": 2,
  "resultados": [
    {
      "n_intento": 1,
      "email": "tomsmith",
      "resultado": "You logged into a secure area!",
      "screenshot": "screenshots/screenshot_1_tomsmith.png"
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Screenshots

Each login attempt automatically generates a screenshot and stores it inside the `screenshots/` directory.

